inn1.comm: huge wide outside off, batman watches it go by
angled at pads, flicked just wide of the man at mid wicket, good running
driven into the covers, but not well timed and easy fielding for Deonarine at extra cover
outside off, full of length, batsman lets it go
again outside off but fails to tempt the batsman
defended out to mid wicket

again defended outside the off stump

forward defensive now as Sibanda breathes again
undecided shot, inside edge and the ball goes past the stumps and beats the keeper, rolls away to the unguarded fine leg boundary
defended down on the leg side

good length delivery, again on the stumps - taps it away on the off side - bit of confusion going for the single but in the end they decide not to go for it
again forced away towards cover, no room for a single there
short of a good length delivery, bit of anlge in - punched off the back-foot and the ball finds the bowler
again slightly short and on the middle and leg stump line, defended watchfully and the ball rolls away on the leg side
left alone outside off, good carry to the keeper
angles in on the pads, worked off the back-foot to the backward square leg region, easy two
drives wide of the fielder at cover
tossed up outside the off stump, defended watchfully
flighted delivery on the middle and leg stump line, defended down on the leg side - no single there
turned away towards square leg
quicker delivery, defended on the front-foot
worked away off the pads to the short fine leg region
flicked away well wide of the fielder at midwicket, easy single
swinging in sharply and the ball rolls away off the pads
full and drifting into middle and leg, Sibanda fails to make contact and the ball crashes into the pad, loud appeal for lbw turned down - was missing leg for sure
in the slot and Sibanda punches it straight back down the track, mid-on had no chance of cutting it off - super shot
glided down to third man
pulled down to mid-on, came off the edge
defended outside the off stump

inn2.comm: what a start ! Smith who is in the middle of a poor form, goes back and defends on the backfoot of a short ball, but misses it and gets hit on on the ribs, and writhes in pain and the ball bounces back onto the pitch and rolls over to the stumps and just knocks the bails off. Smith was shocked to turn around and see the bails dislodged
